connected canonical models implies\nthat we must make a fundamental choice: in which domain we impose a\ndistribution for the inflaton in order to then determine the likelihood of\ninflation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 9 Mar 2019 00:39:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 3 Apr 2019 09:11:09 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 9 Sep 2019 14:28:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
