fter arrival at Pluto's surface, haze\nparticles may be less inert than might be supposed from the low surface\ntemperatures. They must either interact with local materials and environments\nto produce distinct products in different regions, or else the supply of haze\nmust be non-uniform in time and/or location, such that different products are\ndelivered to different places.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 9 Mar 2019 03:33:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-12"}
